review_blob: Lite yellow fizzy piss-tasting brew. Tastes like a cross between corn and the can that it came in. Nothing redeeming whatsoever. Id rather drink Bud Light (which is probably the second worst beer ever brewed).
Hard to describe the "aroma" when what Im smelling is Rice Krispies.  Heavy malt taste, and nothing Id want more than one of.

Bought it at an Acme while visiting family in Akron, OH.  Quite watery for a stout and has a thin head.  Chocolate hint, but more of a roasted malt taste.  Medium palate.  Ill finish the six-pack, but wont likely buy it again.

Stumbled across this beer while in Niagara Falls, and bought it mainly because Im a Steelers fan.  Took several cans home to give to friends but popped one open.  Coincidentally, it tasted an awful lot like Iron City.  

Not bad, and Id drink it again.
An almost undrinkable novelty.  Shouldnt even be called "beer".  I tried this for the first time in the early 90s and frankly cant believe its still around.  Its no better now than it was then.

Almost clear, and tastes like skunky water.  The only time this beer is worth drinking is after a couple of hours of mowing the lawn, and only then if theres absolutely nothing else and no way to get to a bar.  

The stuff smells absolutely awful and comes in 40s - nuff said. 

Lets see - something good about it?  Its cheap.  If youre in college and on a budget... well, it beer.  Kinda.
"Fetid" is probably too strong a word, but this stuff is awful.  Given a choice between Rolling Rock and Kool-Aid (and I actually was given that choice once), I took the Kool-Aid.  Blecch.

Tried it on a recent trip to San Antonio and was pleasantly surprised.  Thought Id be stuck drinking Lone Star, but the bartender offered this as the "local" beer, and it was more German (duh!) than it was Texan.  

Good aroma, medium-dark brown, and went very well with the BBQ I had for dinner that night.

I think you have to have grown up on this stuff to have a real appreciation for it.  Certainly not my everyday beer, but when Im back in the Burgh for a Steelers or Pens game, Im going to Pump an Arn!
Coors Light is what I drink when I want to drink a lot of beer and not get drunk.
Good caramel flavor with a touch of malt.  One of the better porters - almost a dessert beer.
